parameters.prompt:
=Create a product review form. CRITICAL: The questions must be specific to THIS exact product — not generic "rate your purchase" questions.

Product & order context:
- Product: {{ $('Delivery Confirmed Webhook').item.json.body.productName }}
- Category: {{ $('Delivery Confirmed Webhook').item.json.body.category }}
- Subcategory: {{ $('Delivery Confirmed Webhook').item.json.body.subcategory }}
- Brand: {{ $('Delivery Confirmed Webhook').item.json.body.brand }}
- Price: ${{ $('Delivery Confirmed Webhook').item.json.body.price }}
- Product attributes: {{ JSON.stringify($('Delivery Confirmed Webhook').item.json.body.attributes) }}
- Is repeat purchase: {{ $('Delivery Confirmed Webhook').item.json.body.isRepeatPurchase }}
- Customer order count: {{ $('Delivery Confirmed Webhook').item.json.body.totalOrders }}
- Size/variant ordered: {{ $('Delivery Confirmed Webhook').item.json.body.variant || 'N/A' }}

DYNAMIC RULES — form MUST change based on product data:
1. Overall rating (1-5 stars) — always include
2. CATEGORY + SUBCATEGORY specific questions (e.g. Electronics > Headphones: sound quality, comfort; Clothing > Shoes: size accuracy, arch support; Home > Kitchen: ease of cleaning)
3. PRICE-BASED expectations (under $25: value focus; $100+: premium/unboxing experience; $500+: luxury/craftsmanship)
4. If isRepeatPurchase: ask comparison with previous purchase
5. If totalOrders > 5: shorter form (max 4 questions, respect loyal customer time)
6. If totalOrders === 1: include shopping experience and discovery questions
7. If variant exists: ask about variant accuracy
8. Always end with photo upload (optional) + open text review

parameters.jsCode:
// Register this form for webhook monitoring
const formId = $input.first().json.id;
const shareUrl = $input.first().json.shareUrl;
const staticData = $getWorkflowStaticData('global');
const watchedFormIds = staticData.watchedFormIds ?? [];
if (formId && !watchedFormIds.includes(formId)) {
  watchedFormIds.push(formId);
  staticData.watchedFormIds = watchedFormIds;
}
return [{ json: { ...($input.first().json), formId, shareUrl } }];

